steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6nn29","text":"Cells are ready for nucleofection when the culture reaches 70-80% confluency","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5d3f9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bmeei","text":"For a detailed protocol on growing feeder-free hPSCs, refer to the collection \"Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs;\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4mcqu2w","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"482i6","text":"Coat 6-well plates with VTN/Matrigel/Geltrex as depicted in the collection “Feeder-free culturing of hPSCs,\" dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.b4mcqu2w","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b427o","text":"Resuspend cell pellet in 1 ml DMEM/F12, triturate to single cells using P1000 tips","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f4k9a","text":"Take two sets of 10 µl of cell suspension. Mix each set with 10 µl trypan blue dye, which comes with the Countess™ Cell Counting Chamber Slides","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ap8sc","text":"Count cells with Countess automated cell counter or hemocytometer, average the counts from the two sets. Continue with re-suspending the cell pellet in 20 ml nucleofection solution as described in the protocol \"Nucleofection of hPSCs\" (Step 2)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7v2ke","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7lme0","text":"The protocol \"Nucleofection of hPSCs\" can be found in the collection \"Nucleofection (Amaxa) and electroporation (Biorad) of hPSCs.\" A link to this collection can be found in the title section of this protocol, located above.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ja9c","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ctd6a","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"34qni","text":"Mix the cell suspension in the conical tube, take 500,000 cells per nucleofection reaction and transfer to a new conical tube","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b37qr","text":"Aspirate supernatant as much as possible, to minimize the interference to the nucleofection buffer system.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Preparing feeder-free hPSCs for nucleofection
